
=Description=

David Hookes:

"Most significantly, the majority of workers in many advanced economies are now
information workers and expend most energy, for which they receive wages, using
their own information processing and control organ, the brain, rather than their
muscles. A dominant subgroup of the information proletariat, the knowledge workers,
deals in a universal quantity, knowledge, especially scientific and technical
knowledge. Because of this unique position they form the group most aware of the
impending climate and environmental crises. In addition they also possess the skills
and knowledge to create the technologies for alter-globalisation. In order to
implement a program they must, of course, form alliances with all other sections of
the working class."
(http://hometown.aol.co.uk/davehookes/Newyork1.pdf)


